- Emissions reporting & targets: Allstate publicly discloses GHG inventories, third-party verification and year-over-year changes; it committed to net-zero by 2030 for scope 1/2 and relevant value chain emissions and to set financed emissions and Scope 3 targets by end of 2025 [allstatesustainability](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF6Q8ifUUU78Cr0A8p42rF0BcjoqqUohMnX14Xs1GHDH5Z4Tzdv3kNJ8AeijAllK6uP_S5Xw5sVPwDMWkZci4o9XyVkpvB_t0E7TllTTbG83XgB_nDbdCYqm9MmB4OzFuWQbYMfnFiqOf_l8Q==) [allstatenewsroom](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE_ncBJ0f_D5-zX3Zl-SHE5HX7JRVCg5wxKHVO-hEXdiazXmztLSUAWDHCaoa-3_0YI1rb9uJyldqlU8-gGzpn5Pwad2kZtcFsLeIK5Wn2TuNqe2eDoNep4NPkLkIKN07HuF_wEghnPCKRwOIllKONVxUT8Cw9pLUazFKW3K5vdYgAUSFAAWbI-pZjhS4CTq6dW2zrVpsMVLqb2PLa5jwB6ijEbCg==) [esgtoday](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG2CNl1je9FUaOMe36ik7MavGTOLLHON-XU2FxY9zVz0RxWEGcOc5sRm0A7tAYd7NtcajpuZxr2sYphzA2SrS9mzMxrYvZM11_CUe1h234WgK8yMJ0R4Q3INJrVA604Ti-xBOOxYI2_78cNy61swXhOxUO_wkmjvweYyEJYTckbdV3vNSw=).
- Business impact from climate: Allstate reported 124 natural catastrophe events in 2022 totaling $3.1B in losses — a material business impact that underscores why the company is investing in climate resilience and mitigation [allstate](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEdWM6NtzEGSt6zKsl0825gbNjjhUAAkZel_yPUWL8Xz1nybC7wAiZdeK7Te8IJwS4V1FXHljMwD_aNxsAOz9IsHV2x_t8u1DfXzRDzahWea1dS0t5kpcisrocq3rJ2fkvtjeX6rHt4XQ6Z83M0La_-36zUIcEzpFD7gZQwITiqMp43Fygbg6UtedgIkOPwnWpL3b3ooKcpaKg1KgQIxAziWnM=) [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFLh9QrvrKEpQXs48w3rOdbSsfzasZEiwgoJMrNNSL5JJKFpIacHj7Ntb41fD4sp2lpKfrvaiPCr0a5tzwBgrqGu049eftLQcLOAvVzHUP0FGW2Jv8EPg1CyBYR_L06uPhnPv53VdqDG8pBeFoetbPbJ7CnVpS3k4yID3e6hVPjIamxbWm59QIfJlPvPxlYIYOjhrj1Xpxaw-EkPA==).

Why 13/25: There are clear, documented, and quantifiable actions — multi-hundred-million-dollar investment commitments, fleet hybrid percentages, and public GHG reporting — but the measurable environmental outcomes (e.g., percentage reduction in corporate emissions attributable to technology programs, or quantified energy/resource savings or >25% reductions) are not consistently reported as large, standalone technology-driven improvements in the 2022–2025 window. Allstate’s disclosures show progress and significant capital allocation, but not the type of clear documented >25–50% environmental improvements tied directly to specific technology deployments that would earn a higher band [allstateinvestments](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF2X9bI55bCYI_-GpleNuw1mPUTdwnurml_OWJe6nmLRx_bAVSS69xbzSVlnuwY2m9ie4un1CakO5NDpVsWy4PNjENCc_8T2e4m6KbJ1pNuyMvMbqlSFD90tjTQsD9cVVWRP3rYFJH2I1_mYTvzTpwKmRWx-T7U_hJCoaQ=) [csrwindo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG0_i_X2Il0nAdTODEW4ZRtDPgIDjNSq4b0OYJOcmEHV1xEQb_CQtLTqEUItaskF46Zsx9AbE8BatoLwrb7XsFXSD48zH8vsQSQ6zS12_5OqQf-eWN548FDZqIBVt9wHN15HdIsgXJ-BmQ1R81XbWHPzL9AnC_wJgVAiQJJ0hr-HXWu-T_P-42rfPbGIflIyZSFembprPk=) [allstatesustainability](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF6Q8ifUUU78Cr0A8p42rF0BcjoqqUohMnX14Xs1GHDH5Z4Tzdv3kNJ8AeijAllK6uP_S5Xw5sVPwDMWkZci4o9XyVkpvB_t0E7TllTTbG83XgB_nDbdCYqm9MmB4OzFuWQbYMfnFiqOf_l8Q==).

